{
  "stem": "6845.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But otherwise, it was a very happy life, except, again, my mother was so particular how the daughters will be raised.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I don't think they made all this fuss with my two older brothers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But she-- she really went all out the way that it should be special.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So from day one, I guess, after I was born or whenever-- really early-- they get me a governess from the western part of Czechoslovakia, and that I will speak only German, because that was the language of culture.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She wanted to me-- to grow up like a cultured young woman.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And consequently, I didn't learn the Hungarian language, nor the Slovak language, only after age 6.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's when I started public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then my parents spoke to me, from that time on, Hungarian, and in the school, Slovak.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So by the time of I was 7, I spoke all three languages fluently.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was something my mother was very, very much concerned about.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there were lots of things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I could go on forever about my mother, because she was really very unusual.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we would put away, in those days-- I mean, like, 65 years ago-- vegetable for the winter in sand, and-- and cover up, in the-- in the big-- uh, what did we-- what do they-- we call it?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Underground, a-- Cellar?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What is the underground house?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A-- not a cave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had even ice, we put in there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Oh, there's a name for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There is a definite English-- anyway, that's where we kept the vegetables.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in order to go down to this lower level of the house, we had to have a tremendous-- like a 15-inch-long key, and to use that.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
